$takeWhile($greaterThanOne, [5, 5, 5, 1, 5, 5]); // [5, 5, 5]     Parameter  Type  Description      $predicate  callable  callable $predicate Function to use for testing each element    $list  array  array    $list      List to take elements from    return  array  array               First elements of list that all pass the $predicate

Logical Or Combinator  :: (a -  Bool) -  (a -  Bool) -  (a -  Bool)  Given two functions f and g, combine them in such a way to produce a new
function h that returns true given f(x) OR g(x) returns true.  $funcF = function($x) { return $x  = 5; };
$funcG = function($x) { return $x == 0; };

$combinator = $orCombinator($funcF, $funcG);

$combinator(9); // True
$combinator(0); // True
